<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 3:00PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Lapeer
and northwestern St. Clair Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 300 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Capac, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Emmett around 305 PM EDT.
Yale around 320 PM EDT.
Other locations impacted by this storm include Riley Center,
Allenton, Avoca, Jeddo, Fargo, Berville, Lynn Township and Brockway.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
